00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,240
Charles likes music.

76
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,760
Charles likes kuss.

77
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:10,400
No.

78
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,000
He likes it, huh?

79
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,120
Yami! Yami!

80
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:20,240
You know I turn into a Lion
when anybody tickles me.

81
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,840
Seriously.

82
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:36,440
[If you are from outside of Mexico,
what document allows you to work in this country?]

83
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,280
The hardest thing?

84
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:55,440
To think that...

85
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,040
...I don't know...

86
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,400
...that I'll run out of possibilities...

87
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:06,680
...to keep fighting, to keep them all afloat.

88
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:11,200
That's the hardest thing for me.

89
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,120
Ok, did you bring the
papers we asked for?

90
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:27,520
Well, they are kind of incomplete because...

91
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:30,760
...I'm not from here, you see.
They're partly done.

92
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,280
Where are you from?

93
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,680
I'm from Honduras.

94
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:38,920
Ok. So your papers aren't sorted
for you to work here?

95
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,720
No, they haven't been processed yet.

96
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:56,040
The thing is that I'm from Honduras and...

97
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:59,120
...that's why I can't get a job here but I need it.

98
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,560
I need to work.

99
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:06,000
But...why don't you get your papers first?

100
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,640
Didn't he move?

101
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:31,200
Yes.

102
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,120
He's always moving.

103
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,200
Did you feel pain today?

104
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,280
No, not now.

105
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:44,320
Only when he moves a lot,
but no. No pain today.

106
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,080
A kick?

107
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:58,560
He won't move, if you're touching him.

108
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:04,520
Too bad, when he wants me to carry him I won't.

109
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,680
Hello

110
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:20,640
Hi son.

111
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,000
How are you Mum?

112
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,400
Ok son, good evening.

113
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,800
How have you been?

114
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,440
Good honey, and you?

115
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,000
Good, thank God.

116
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,240
And the kids?

117
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,640
They're there playing.

118
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:32,520
David...

119
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:33,200
And Rocio?

120
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:33,720
What?

121
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,560
Rocio was watching TV downstairs I think.

122
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,040
Ahh.

123
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:39,760
On Tuesday?

124
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:40,520
What?

125
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,120
Everything ok?

126
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,640
Yes, thank God, yes.

127
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,400
And...on Tuesday, right?

128
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,320
On Tuesday, they'll say something, right?

129
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,120
Yes son.

130
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,400
We have to wait.

131
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:55,040
Be strong, don't fall apart.

132
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,320
You have to keep going.

133
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:00,680
You know I love you and I'm very grateful.

134
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:03,000
Yes, don't worry about that.

135
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:07,760
Sometimes Rocio drives me crazy
but we're getting by.

136
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:14,000
You know she's a teenager.
She's at that age.

137
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,000
I know.

138
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,560
The phone card is running out. I'll call you tomorrow.

139
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:19,360
Ok.

140
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,160
Be good honey. Good night.

141
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,720
Do you need anything there?

142
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:24,920
No honey.

143
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,440
Paper or something?

144
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:31,120
No son. The girls gave me some food and biscuits.

145
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:31,920
Ok.

146
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,000
Ok son, good night.

147
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,240
What scares me?

148
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,080
What scares me is...

149
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:15,120
...the idea that my mum gets
an extremely long sentence...

150
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,400
...and she can't get out again...

151
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:22,360
...or she dies of sadness in there.

152
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,320
Hello?

153
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,360
Hi Mummy!

154
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:28,920
I'm ok.

155
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:30,320
Here they are!

156
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,600
She's asking for her good looking son.

157
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,880
But Ale isn't here.

158
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,640
He's not here.

159
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,360
It's a joke! Here he is.

160
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,680
Take it David.

161
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,560
Hello Mummy.

162
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:48,280
Jumping, jumping, pum, pum.

163
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:53,640
What is it? Do you think that's funny?

164
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,880
Do you think that's funny?

165
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,280
Yes, it's funny!

166
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,800
It's not funny!

167
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:07,400
Yes it's funny!

168
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,680
It's not.

169
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,800
Yes it's funny!

170
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,840
It's not.

171
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:23,760
It's not funny! It's very funny!

172
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,320
It's a joke, it's not.

173
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:33,600
It's not funny or very funny.

174
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,320
It's super funny!

175
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,640
It's mum.This time it's for real. Wait outside.

176
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,080
Hello?

177
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,280
Hi Mummy!

178
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,320
Hi sweetie! How are you honey?

179
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,120
Good.

180
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,720
They gave you the news, right?

181
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:54,480
What news?

182
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,680
They sentenced me.

183
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,760
No Mummy...how long?

184
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,680
Ten years honey.

185
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:01,640
No Mummy...don't say that.

186
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,760
Yes sweetie, there's nothing I can do.

187
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,480
Justice isn't for everybody.

188
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:12,360
Maybe because we're immigrants;
I have to pay for it.

189
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:15,320
But the true criminals are outside.

190
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,440
Don't tell me it's ten years.

191
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:20,680
Ten years darling,
it's unfair but what can we do?

192
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,280
No.

193
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,440
Do you know what's the important thing here?

194
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:28,040
That you know I never did anything wrong.

195
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:32,320
I feel proud about that and
I want you to feel proud too.

196
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,800
I want you to look forward...

197
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:36,800
...and no one will destroy you
pshycologicaly or morally.

198
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,720
You have the ability.

199
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:43,520
You and Alejandro are the older ones, and
you have the ability.

200
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:44,840
Mummy...

201
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,760
Yes?

202
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:47,320
...thank you.

203
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,800
Why honey?

204
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:51,320
For everything you gave us.

205
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,920
No honey, it's my duty.

206
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,760
It's my duty to care for you...

207
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:04,920
...but now the cirmcustances are keeping us apart.

208
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,240
We won't get the time back...

209
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:13,520
...but I'll come out stronger from here
to give you the things you need.

210
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:18,920
I promise I'll make up for the time.

211
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,840
I promise.

212
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,200
With God's will we'll make it; you'll see.

213
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,320
I swear.

214
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:28,760
Remember when I used to
ring you in Honduras...

215
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:32,600
...and told you I was going to bring you here?

216
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,400
I kept my promise.

217
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,920
This time too I was going to keep my promise...

218
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,600
...because I was about to leave this place...

219
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,240
...because all the evidence
was in my favour.

220
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,000
But in the end, the law didn't see it that way.

221
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:49,120
But...

222
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,160
...if we have faith...

223
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,640
...everything will be ok; you'll see.

224
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,080
Yes.

225
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,440
I love you honey.

226
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:02,240
Yes.

227
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:01,120
I thought you weren't going to bring me.

228
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:07,720
Do you want me to tell the driver to stop
and let you get out?

229
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,200
Huh?

230
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:15,360
I take responsibilities to make your life easier.

231
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,880
I have to take the role of the father here.

232
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:24,720
You overdo it.

233
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:30,480
I have to work. If I don't we won't have food the next day.

234
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:33,520
They donate  food to the house Alejandro.

235
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:36,720
I know Rocio, but we can't live off beans all our lives.

236
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,440
You see? Now you get it!

237
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,360
I've been telling you for months...

238
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:43,320
...that beans and rice isn't the best food.

239
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:04,280
And now?

240
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:06,280
This is what we'll do.

241
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,480
We won't tell mum about this...

242
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:12,280
...because if we tell her she'll worry.

243
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,920
I don't want her to get ill...

244
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,880
...especially in there.

245
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,200
I love you a lot.

246
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,760
I love you very very much.

247
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,240
You can't imagine it.

248
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,000
I love you too.

249
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,840
I want you to promise me...

250
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:40,120
...that we're going to make this family work
till the day Mum gets out.

251
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,680
I hope that'll be soon.

252
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,240
I want her to find a united family.

253
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,480
Can you promise me that?

254
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,720
Are we going to help each other?

255
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,880
Give me a hug.

256
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,600
Are you sure they'll let this in?

257
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,400
Yeah, maybe.

258
00:17:55,720 --> 00:18:00,440
One year and four months later

259
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:49,080
If we go at 120km per hour...

260
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:54,560
My mum has now been in jail
for two years and four months.

261
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:58,120
Since she was put in jail...

262
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:04,600
...I haven't been doing very well
in my relationship with myself.

263
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:10,600
Sometimes I think,
why am I always answering back to my brother?

264
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,680
But sometimes I say to myself,
it's not my fault!

265
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:17,840
It's obvious. I'm at an age where I think
I'm the queen of the world...

266
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,640
...but I'm not.

267
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:24,520
I don't know how to explain how I feel...

268
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,680
I'm confused.

269
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:55,480
Austin...

270
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:59,120
Look...

271
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,000
Do you want a sweet?

272
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:24,760
Children...

273
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:27,040
