00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:32,640
Be optimistic.

544
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:37,560
And lift up that self-esteem that
you've always had so much of.

545
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:41,720
Better times will come, son.
Don't fall apart.

546
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:49,240
Well Mum, I'm going home now
because I just finished work.

547
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:51,240
I'm a bit tired and hungry.

548
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:54,920
I'll call you later then, or tomorrow;
because I don't have a phone card.

549
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:55,880
Ok.

550
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:58,480
Well son I love you very much, alright?

551
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,560
I love you too.

552
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:01,720
I love you honey.

553
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,080
You think, why is this happening to me?

554
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:21,440
You see the people around you and think...

555
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,480
...why me?...

556
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:33,200
...with so many people in the world.

557
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:37,160
There are people more miserable than me.

558
00:39:37,240 --> 00:39:40,160
They're in worse situations.

559
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:46,520
And you feel pity.

560
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:52,920
You feel sometimes...I don't know.

561
00:39:54,120 --> 00:39:57,040
More than pity,
you feel sorry for those people;...

562
00:39:57,080 --> 00:40:00,320
...because you know what it's like.

563
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:06,160
And people who've never gone through
such serious problems...

564
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:48,600
...sometimes they underestimate
what they've got.

565
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:55,720
You look pretty.

566
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:03,440
...you're like a happy teddy bear.

567
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:23,520
Here is your coconut milkshake.

568
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,920
I'll give you shit milkshake...

569
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:39,800
It doesn't want to go in!

570
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:41,840
Bloody thing!

571
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:46,800
I don't like these plates,
they don't want to be clean!

572
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:04,840
Now.

573
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:13,600
Bravo!

574
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:39,200
Hello.

575
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:47,720
Why did you arrive so late?

576
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:53,120
I went for a walk with my friends.

577
00:43:58,040 --> 00:43:59,560
Who did you ask for permission?

578
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:04,040
Noboby. I know I didn't ask for permission
but I get bored here Alejandro.

579
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:08,360
Is that your excuse for going out
anytime you want?

580
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:15,160
No, but you know I feel like
a slave here with the children.

581
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,280
Turn down the TV a bit please.

582
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:33,600
What am I gonna do with you Rocio?

583
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:35,280
I'm sorry Ale.

584
00:44:36,160 --> 00:44:37,360
I'm sorry, that's all?

585
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:41,840
I'll say sorry and that's it. He'll forget everything.

586
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:47,880
I know where you were.

587
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:54,640
If I wanted I could have gone there
and dragged you back by your hair...

588
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:57,880
...to make you feel embarrassed...

589
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:03,200
...and scream at you there.

590
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:05,520
Would you like me to go there
and scream at you?

591
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:07,720
...ask you why you went out
without permission?

592
00:45:07,840 --> 00:45:08,560
No.

593
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:18,800
Imagine, one of these days Mummy calls
and I don't know where you are.

594
00:45:19,040 --> 00:45:23,200
And I say, "I don't know Mummy,
I don't know where she is"

595
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:28,160
"And Rocio?" I don't know. She went out
without permission.

596
00:45:29,080 --> 00:45:30,240
"Where? Who with?"

597
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:33,520
"I don't know because she does her own thing."

598
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:38,000
Can I come in to watch TV?

599
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:40,040
No Rocio. Go to bed.

600
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:11,280
They say Mexico has one of the most
transparent judicial systems

601
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:14,120
It won a prize for it,

602
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:16,880
but...

603
00:46:18,320 --> 00:46:22,640
I realize it won that for the Mexicans,

604
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:24,560
but because we're not from Mexico...

605
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:26,600
...we are like an old rag for them.

606
00:46:26,720 --> 00:46:29,360
They use us, squeeze us and throw us away.

607
00:46:29,440 --> 00:46:31,160
It's not my brother and sister's fault.

608
00:46:31,240 --> 00:46:32,240
It's not our fault.

609
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:34,080
It's not even my Mum's fault.

610
00:46:34,120 --> 00:46:38,840
My Mum isn't guilty for
having wanted a better life for us.

611
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:43,920
I can't take a situation like this.

612
00:46:45,520 --> 00:46:47,920
Well my mum's sentence is unfair.

613
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:50,360
My only hope is that one day...

614
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:55,280
...they'll discover the truth
and she'll be released sooner,...

615
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:58,240
...only if that happens.

616
00:47:40,080 --> 00:47:41,160
Hello?

617
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:46,360
Really?

618
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:49,920
Ay Mummy! I want to cry right now.

619
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:50,640
Me too!

620
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:51,760
But out of happiness.

621
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:57,920
Take care and be good.

622
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:01,240
Here they are.

623
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:02,240
Put them on.

624
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:04,400
There you go.

625
00:48:06,440 --> 00:48:07,120
Who's that?

626
00:48:08,360 --> 00:48:08,920
Yami.

627
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:16,120
Hello Mummy.

628
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:17,040
Hello honey.

629
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:19,080
Are you happy?

630
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:19,840
Yes.

631
00:48:23,680 --> 00:48:24,240
Hello.

632
00:48:24,680 --> 00:48:25,480
Hello darling.

633
00:48:27,840 --> 00:48:31,760
Yes, Gaby told me a while ago.
I didn't know anything.

634
00:48:49,720 --> 00:48:51,040
Is the cream...

635
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:54,160
...wet?

636
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:55,400
No.

637
00:48:56,520 --> 00:48:58,360
You have a bit there.

638
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:00,560
Here.

639
00:49:01,680 --> 00:49:03,040
There, on your hand.

640
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:33,160
Is that her?

641
00:49:45,080 --> 00:49:46,720
Mummy!

642
00:49:47,200 --> 00:49:48,840
Mummy!

643
00:49:58,760 --> 00:50:00,760
It's over now, at last.

644
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:01,600
Yes.

645
00:50:12,120 --> 00:50:14,120
It's over now, at last.

646
00:50:14,880 --> 00:50:16,880
At last. It's over.

647
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:35,200
Wait! Wait!

648
00:50:35,280 --> 00:50:37,560
Let's take a photo, come on!

649
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:41,720
Smile!
You have to smile...

650
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:44,000
...because this is a happy moment.

651
00:50:50,040 --> 00:50:51,880
Let's go home.

652
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,600
What are we going to eat?

653
00:50:58,360 --> 00:51:00,360
Rice and beans!

654
00:51:02,200 --> 00:51:04,040
No, burgers.

655
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:06,480
What do you want them with?

656
00:51:18,440 --> 00:51:27,280
Alejandro and Rocio's mother was accused
of extortion and involvement in organized crime.

657
00:51:29,440 --> 00:51:36,320
After 2 years and 4 months in prison
she was released due to lack of evidence.
